text: Chak Thathai is a village in Arifwala tehsil in the Pakpattan district of Punjab province, Pakistan. The village's population was 8,535 at the time of the 1998 census, 8,504 of whom were categorised as Muslim. Thathai is also the name of the wider union council area, which had a recorded population of 22,635 in 1998. == References == Category:Villages in Pakpattan District
